## Workflow 2 — Attendance Alert to Parents

### Overview

When a student is marked **absent**, the system immediately notifies the parent via WhatsApp so they are aware.

### Trigger

| Property | Value |
|---|---|
| Type | **Event-driven** |
| Event | `attendance/marked` (fired after `POST /attendance/:batchId` succeeds) |
| Payload | `{ batchId, date, records: [{studentId, status}], teacherId }` |

```
Teacher marks attendance
  → API writes to Firestore
  → API emits event: attendance/marked
  → Inngest receives event
  → Fan-out: one sub-job per absent student
```

### Workflow Steps

```
[EVENT]: attendance/marked
│
├─ Step 1: filter-absent-students
│    Filter records: status == "absent"
│    If none → exit early (no-op)
│
├─ Step 2: fetch-student-details (parallel batch)
│    For each absentStudentId:
│      Read Firestore: students/{id} → { name, parentPhone, fcmToken }
│
├─ Step 3: send-alerts (parallel)
│    For each absent student:
│    ├─ Step 3a: send-whatsapp → parentPhone
│    └─ Step 3b: log-alert → Firestore automationLogs
│
└─ Step 4: no-duplicate-guard
     Check: was an alert already sent today for this student+batch?
     (Idempotency key: teacherId + batchId + studentId + date)
     If yes → skip silently
```

### Retry Policy

```
maxAttempts: 3
backoff: exponential (30s → 2 min → 8 min)
timeout: 10 minutes total per workflow
```

### Message Template

**WhatsApp (parent):**
```
📋 Attendance Update

Dear Parent of {{studentName}},

Your child was marked *ABSENT* in today's class.

📚 Batch: {{batchName}}
📅 Date: {{date}} ({{dayOfWeek}})
⏰ Class Time: {{classTime}}

If this is an error, please contact the teacher.

— {{teacherName}} Sir/Ma'am
({{teacherPhone}})
```

> **Note:** Only fires for `absent`. `present` and `holiday` do not trigger alerts (prevents notification fatigue).

