## Workflow 4 — Announcement Broadcast

### Overview

When a teacher publishes an announcement, the system broadcasts it to all target recipients via the selected channels (in-app, WhatsApp) in parallel, with delivery tracking.

### Trigger

| Property | Value |
|---|---|
| Type | **Event-driven** (immediate or scheduled) |
| Event | `announcement/published` |
| Payload | `{ announcementId, teacherId, targetBatchId, channels[], scheduledAt }` |

```
Teacher creates announcement → POST /announcements
  If scheduledAt == null:
    → Emit: announcement/published immediately
  If scheduledAt != null:
    → Inngest sleeps until scheduledAt, then fires
```

### Workflow Steps

```
[EVENT]: announcement/published
│
├─ Step 1: fetch-announcement
│    Read Firestore: announcements/{id} → title, message, targetBatchId, channels
│
├─ Step 2: resolve-recipients
│    If targetBatchId:
│      → Fetch enrolled students of that batch
│    Else:
│      → Fetch ALL active students of the teacher
│    Build list: [{ name, parentPhone, fcmToken, studentPhone }]
│
├─ Step 3: fan-out by channel (parallel)
│    ├─ [if "whatsapp"]: generate-wa-links (Step 3a)
│    │    Build wa.me deep-link for each parentPhone
│    │    Store links in announcement.whatsappLinks[]
│    │
│    └─ [if "inapp"]: send-fcm-batch (Step 3b)
│         Batch FCM multicast (up to 500 tokens per call)
│         Log delivery receipt per token
│
├─ Step 4: update-announcement-status
│    Write: { status: "sent", sentAt, recipientCount, fcmDelivered, fcmFailed }
│
└─ Step 5: log-audit
     Write automationLog: type "announcement", announcementId, channels, sentCount
```

### Message Template

**FCM Push (in-app notification):**
```
Title: 📢 {{title}}
Body:  {{messageTruncated150}}
Data:  { screen: "announcements", id: "{{announcementId}}" }
```

**WhatsApp (deep links — teacher sends manually via generated links):**
```
📢 *{{title}}*

{{message}}

— {{teacherName}} Sir/Ma'am
```

> **WhatsApp note**: The system generates pre-filled `wa.me` links (one per parent). The teacher opens WhatsApp and taps "Send" — no WhatsApp Business API required for Phase 1. Phase 2 can upgrade to Cloud API for fully automated sends.

### Schedule Support

```
Immediate:   scheduledAt == null → fires on publish
Scheduled:   scheduledAt set    → Inngest sleeps, fires at scheduledAt
Recurrence:  Not supported in v1 (future: RRULE-based cron per announcement)
```

---

## Workflow 5 — Payment Confirmation Message

### Overview

When a fee record is marked as **paid** or **partial**, automatically send a payment receipt / confirmation to the student's parent via WhatsApp.

### Trigger

| Property | Value |
|---|---|
| Type | **Event-driven** |
| Event | `fee/payment.recorded` |
| Payload | `{ feeRecordId, studentId, batchId, amount, paidAmount, paymentMode, paidAt, teacherId }` |

```
Teacher marks fee as paid → PATCH /fees/:id/pay
  → API updates Firestore
  → API emits: fee/payment.recorded
  → Inngest receives event → sends confirmation
```

### Workflow Steps

```
[EVENT]: fee/payment.recorded
│
├─ Step 1: fetch-details (parallel)
│    ├─ Read FeeRecord: amount, paidAmount, balance, month, paymentMode
│    ├─ Read Student: name, parentPhone, fcmToken
│    └─ Read Teacher: name, phone
│
├─ Step 2: determine-receipt-type
│    If balance == 0 → type: "full_payment"
│    If balance > 0  → type: "partial_payment"
│
├─ Step 3: send-confirmation (parallel)
│    ├─ Step 3a: send-whatsapp → parentPhone
│    └─ Step 3b: send-fcm-push → student device (if token exists)
│
├─ Step 4: generate-receipt-id
│    receiptId = "REC-{{teacherCode}}-{{YYYYMM}}-{{feeRecordId_last6}}"
│
└─ Step 5: log-confirmation
     Write automationLog: type "payment_confirmation", feeRecordId, receiptId
     Update FeeRecord: { lastReceiptSentAt, receiptId }
```

### Message Templates

**Full Payment — WhatsApp (parent):**
```
✅ Payment Received

Dear Parent of {{studentName}},

We have received your fee payment. Thank you!

🆔 Receipt No: {{receiptId}}
📚 Batch: {{batchName}}
🗓️ For Month: {{month}}
💰 Amount Paid: ₹{{paidAmount}}
💳 Mode: {{paymentMode}}
📅 Date: {{paidAt}}

Your balance is: *₹0 (Cleared)* ✔️

— {{teacherName}} Sir/Ma'am
({{teacherPhone}})
```

**Partial Payment — WhatsApp (parent):**
```
💳 Partial Payment Recorded

Dear Parent of {{studentName}},

We have recorded your partial fee payment.

🆔 Receipt No: {{receiptId}}
📚 Batch: {{batchName}}
🗓️ For Month: {{month}}
💰 Amount Paid: ₹{{paidAmount}}
💰 Total Fee:  ₹{{totalAmount}}
⚠️ Balance Due: *₹{{balance}}*
💳 Mode: {{paymentMode}}

Please clear the remaining amount at the earliest.

— {{teacherName}} Sir/Ma'am
({{teacherPhone}})
```

**FCM Push (student app):**
```
Title: ✅ Payment Confirmed — {{month}}
Body:  ₹{{paidAmount}} received for {{batchName}}. Receipt: {{receiptId}}
Data:  { screen: "fees", feeRecordId: "{{feeRecordId}}" }
```

